      • checkConnectivityOfPolygonPatches

        protected boolean checkConnectivityOfPolygonPatches(org.deegree.geometry.Geometry geom)
                                             throws java.lang.Exception
        Checks that multiple polygon patches within a surface are connected.

        The test is implemented as follows: Each polygon patch is converted into a JTS Polygon. Then the union of all polygons is created. If the union geometry is a JTS Polygon then the surface is connected - otherwise it is not.

        Checks:

        • Surface (including PolyhedralSurface, CompositeSurface, and OrientableSurface)
        • Only PolygonPatch is allowed as surface patch - all surfaces that contain a different type of surface patch are ignored.
        • The elements of multi and composite geometries (except Multi- and CompositeSolids).
        Does NOT check the surfaces within solids!
        Parameters:
        geom -
        Returns:
        true if the given geometry is a connected surface, a point, a curve, multi- or composite geometry that only consists of these geometry types, else false. Thus, false will be returned whenever a solid is encountered and if a surface is not connected.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • checkNoRepetitionInCurveSegment

        protected boolean checkNoRepetitionInCurveSegment(org.deegree.geometry.Geometry geom)
        Checks that two consecutive points in a posList - within a CurveSegment - are not equal.

        Checks:

        • Curve (including CompositeCurve, LineString, OrientableCurve, Ring)
        • The following CurveSegment types: Arc, ArcString, CubicSpline, GeodesicString, LineStringSegment
        • The exterior and interior rings of polygon patches (contained within Surface, Polygon, PolyhedralSurface, TriangulatedSurface, Tin, CompositeSurface, or OrientableSurface) - NOTE: all other types of surface patches are currently ignored!
        • The elements of multi and composite geometries
        Does NOT check curve segments within solids!
        Parameters:
        geom - the geometry that shall be tested
        Returns:
        true if no repetition was detected (or if the geometry is a point, a solid, or consists of solids), else false
